reviews.review: The majority of the flaws of this movie stem from the overall failure that was The Last Jedi and its overall anemic story.
c'mon Poe and Finn are clearly in love, so that should have been included in the final sequence

Though many will still find the dark side in this movie, I personally believe it to be the best of the 3 new trilogies. JJ wraps up the Saga in the best way possible, and does so even while fixing the mistakes made in The Last Jedi. There was never a dull moment in this movie, and the visuals/ storytelling were top notch. Though, like any movie, its not perfect and there are definitely some plot holes to be discussed, but overall, an amazing film with an uncanny group of talented actors who bring this story, to an end.

wow what a mess, what an awful, non-sensical, frantic, disrespectful way to end this wonderful franchise which is so dear to so many of us.. I cannot believe they did this .. like this.....The Fall of Star Wars.
One of the most entertaining movies to culminate one of the most entertaining franchises. This movie could have been longer, it felt like a rollercoaster physically and emotionally. Masterpiece.

This was a whirlwind of emotion and action. From the new generation to the familiar faces of the past, I was enthralled! I shed tears during and continued to on the way home. I had moments of elation, even a few chuckles. It was super intense and beautiful. See it more times, I will. A larger than life conclusion to a lineage that will survive the ages. I look forward to seeing where we go from here!

I did enjoy the movie so much, it has some things that I didn't like and others that I love but without question is the best of this trilogy, my advice is watch the movie without prejudices and several times if is possible so you can appreciate some details that you can skip in the first viewed. I had a really good time in the cinema with this movie.

Absolutely loved it. By far the best of the sequel trilogy. It just all felt right for the true fan. Coming from someone who reads the books, the comics and has gone to the past two Star Wars Celebrations I absolutely loved all of it. It felt like it could be longer. Perfect amount of nostalgia while mixing in some new from the books that just felt natural and rich.
